issue.title: Create comprehensive migration strategy for mixin fields (#195)
issue.body:
## Summary

Implements a comprehensive migration strategy for safely applying mixin fields to existing Django models as requested in issue #195.

### Key Components Delivered:

âœ… **21 Migration Safety Tests** (`core/tests/test_migration_strategy.py`)
- Data preservation across forward/backward migrations  
- Default value application and audit field population
- Data integrity maintenance (FK constraints, unique constraints, cascades)
- Edge case handling (null values, long names, user deletion, timestamps)
- Performance testing with realistic data volumes (up to 100 objects)
- Concurrency testing for post-migration behavior
- Rollback safety and atomicity verification
- Audit trail integration testing

âœ… **Data Migration Files** (addresses audit field population)
- `characters/migrations/0004_populate_audit_fields.py` - Uses `player_owner` for audit fields
- `items/migrations/0004_populate_audit_fields.py` - Uses `campaign.owner` for audit fields  
- `locations/migrations/0004_populate_audit_fields.py` - Uses `campaign.owner` for audit fields
- All migrations include proper rollback functionality

âœ… **Automated Rollback Script** (`scripts/rollback_mixin_migrations.sh`)
- Interactive safety confirmations
- Step-by-step rollback process (data migrations first, then schema)
- Environment detection and progress reporting
- Complete rollback of both schema (0003) and data (0004) migrations

âœ… **Comprehensive Documentation** (`docs/MIGRATION_STRATEGY.md`)
- Pre-migration checklists and safety procedures
- Step-by-step production deployment guidelines
- Post-migration validation procedures
- Performance considerations and monitoring guidance
- Troubleshooting section with common issues and solutions

### Migration Strategy Overview:

**Schema Migrations (0003):**
- Add `created_by`, `modified_by` fields to Character, Item, Location models
- Update timestamp field configurations for proper indexing
- Enhance name field with standardized help text

**Data Migrations (0004):**  
- Populate audit fields with sensible defaults for existing records
- Characters: Use `player_owner` (most logical ownership)
- Items/Locations: Use `campaign.owner` (campaign-level resources)
- Atomic operations with proper error handling

### Testing Results:
- **All 1210 tests passing** âœ… (including the 21 new migration safety tests)
- **Zero regressions** - All existing functionality preserved
- **Migration safety validated** - Data preservation, integrity, and rollback confirmed

### Production Safety Features:
- Comprehensive test coverage ensuring zero data loss
- Multiple rollback options (automated script + manual procedures)
- Performance testing validates migrations complete in reasonable time
- Edge case testing covers real-world scenarios (user deletion, constraints, etc.)

### Documentation Updates:
- Enhanced `docs/development-guide.md` with migration testing procedures
- Updated `docs/database-schema.md` with migration strategy documentation
- Enhanced `docs/deployment.md` with production migration procedures
- Integrated with existing `CLAUDE.md` development workflow

## Test Plan

âœ… Migration safety tests (21 tests) - All passing
âœ… Full test suite (1210 tests) - All passing  
âœ… Data preservation verified
âœ… Rollback procedures tested
âœ… Documentation comprehensive and validated

Tame Chat Action / Pet Chat Action (stances/commands)

Hello everyone,

I am on a quest to make bot's pets completely functional, focuses on solving issues #1351 , #1230 , and #1137 . This PR achieves the following:

1. Changes the current "pet" chat command to "tame", which is more intuitive that only hunters can use it. The modes are "tame name (name)", "tame id (id)", "tame family (family)", "tame rename (new name)", and "tame abandon". Tame abandon is new - it simply abandons the current pet. Also, now, if you type in "tame family" by itself, it will list the available families. See pictures below for examples.
2. Added new "pet" chat command, with the following modes: "pet passive", "pet aggressive", "pet defensive", "pet stance" (shows current pet stance), "pet attack", "pet follow", and "pet stay". Previously, the pet's stance was not changeable, and there were some less than desired effects from summonable pets - see the issues above.
3. New config option: AiPlayerbot.DefaultPetStance, which changes the stance that all bot's pets are summoned as. This makes sure when feral spirits or treants are summoned by shamans and druids, they are immediately set to this configured stance. Set as 1 as default, which is defensive. (0 = Passive, 1 = Defensive, 2 = Aggressive)
4. New config option: AiPlayerbot.PetChatCommandDebug, which enables debug messages for the "pet" chat command. By default it is set to 0, which is disabled, but if you would like to see when pet's stances are changed, or when you tell the pet to attack/follow/stay, and when pet spells are auto-toggled, this is an option. I made this for myself mainly to test the command - if anyone notices any wierd pet behavior, this will be an option to help them report it as well.
5. Modified FollowActions to not constantly execute the petfollow action, overriding any stay or attack commands issued.
6. Modified GenericActions to have TogglePetSpellAutoCastAction optionally log when spells are toggled based on AiPlayerbot.PetChatCommandDebug.
7. Modified PetAttackAction to not attack if the pet is set to passive, and not override the pet's stance to passive every time it was executed.
8. Modified CombatStrategy.cpp to not constantly issue the petattack command, respecting the "pet stay" and "pet follow" commands. Pets will still automatically attack the enemy if set to aggressive or defensive.
9. Warlocks, Priests, Hunters, Shamans, Mages, Druids, and DKs (all classes that have summons): Added a "new pet" trigger that executes the "set pet stance" action. The "new pet" trigger happens only once, upon summoning a pet. It sets the pet's stance from AiPlayerbot.DefaultPetStance's value.
